ion. They look at individual e-mails more than any mass e-mail.<br>
<br>
So here is what I suggest.  Everyone email them basicly the same e-mail.  I know a lot of you well disagree with some of the things I have suggested.  But we need to start shouting about the problems in our class.  It seems no one at Verant plays a Necro.  So we need to be more vocal!!<br>
<br>
eqfeedback@soe.sony.com = EQ Feed Back : The main e-mail address for Verant.  This will hopefully get sent to the right person.<br>
<br>
eqmail@soe.sony.com = EQ Mail :  One way e-mail you will not get any response.  But they seem to look at this more than anything.<br>
<br>
Subject: A Few Suggestions for the Necromancer Class<br>
<br>
Dear Verant Support,<br>
Over all I’m pleased with the Necromancer Class.  I have been playing for over a year.  In the new release I see a lot of damage over time spells and pet spells. I have a few suggestions about the Necromancer Class:<br>
<br>
Group Spells:<br>
Upgrade to the Screaming Terror Line.<br>
A group Damage Shield with lifetap effect.<br>
Our Debuff line of spells need to be looked at for resist checks.<br>
More efficient mana transfer.<br>
<br>
Raiding:<br>
Upgrade to the Screaming Terror Line.<br>
A group Damage Shield with lifetap effect.<br>
Our Debuff line of spells looked at for resist checks.<br>
More efficient mana transfer.<br>
Hate increasing spells<br>
Hate reducing spells<br>
Better Health transfer<br>
More group buffs in general<br>
<br>
Solo:<br>
Nothing<br>
<br>
<br>
This is what I sent Verant.  I suggest if you dont want someone else speaking for you about changes to the Necro Class sent them your thoughts.<br>
